    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">尸體</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>BODY of a HUMAN OR ANIMAL who has DIED.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The general dignified term for a dead body is shī 尸 / 屍 often in connection with burial.</p>
<p>2. Piǎo 殍 refers specifically to the dead bodies of those who have starved and who lie unburied.</p>
<p>3. Sǐ 死 refers to the dead body of a deceased person in a neutral way, not necessarily in connection with burial.</p>
<p>4. Fá 伐 is a a standard OBI word for decapitated human victims, but this usage became obsolete.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>尸體</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
